#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:1
msgid "Functions & Methods"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:3
msgid "Avoid boolean arguments (`no-bool-args`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:5
msgid ""
"A boolean parameter that selects between two behaviors signals the function "
"does two things. Split it into two functions or use a typed enum."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:11
msgid "// Good — two separate functions\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:14
msgid "// Good — typed enum\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:18
msgid "// Bad — boolean argument\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:23
msgid "See also: _Clean Code_, Chapter 3 \"Flag Arguments\"."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:26
msgid "Use block expressions to scope temporary state (`block-expressions`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:28
msgid ""
"Use block expressions when temporary variables are only needed to produce "
"one final value. This keeps temporary state local and avoids leaking one-off "
"names into outer scope."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:35
msgid "// Good — intermediate values are scoped to the block\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:41
msgid "// Bad — temporary variables leak into outer scope\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:48
msgid "Minimize nesting (`minimize-nesting`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:50
msgid ""
"Minimize nesting depth. Code nested more than three levels deep should be "
"reviewed for refactoring opportunities. Each nesting level multiplies the "
"reader's cognitive load."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:55
msgid "Techniques for flattening nesting:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:56
msgid "Early returns and guard clauses for error paths."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:57
msgid "`let...else` to collapse `if let` chains."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:58
msgid "The `?` operator for error propagation."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:59
msgid "`continue` to skip loop iterations."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:60
msgid "Extracting the nested body into a helper function."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md:62
msgid ""
"The normal/expected code path should be the first visible path; error and "
"edge cases should be handled and dismissed early."
msgstr ""

